                              <condition>The roll is stained and rubbed from heavy physical use and the text is so faded as to be almost illegible. Don C. Skemer speculates 
                                 that the dozen or so irregular brownish spots on the roll may be congealed blood from its role as an amulet duing childbirth. After use, 
                                 Skemer suggests that the roll was washed in water, which explains the loss of text (<title>Binding Words: Textual Amulets in the Middle Ages</title> 
                                 [Pennsylvania State University Press, 2006], pp. 260-261)</condition>
                              
